<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Frederick A. Aldrich lived in Flint, Michigan, and served as an officer in the 3rd Regiment of the Michigan State Troops (later the National Guard) during the late 1880s and early 1890s.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection has been arranged into a single Military Career series of papers and documents.  Included are official correspondence, general orders, receipts and invoices, and miscellaneous.  The collection also includes one photograph from around 1890 of members of the Michigan State Troops taken at Island Lake.</p>
</scopecontent>

